The paper deals with a massive MIMO network and focuses on the pilot sequence design, which is a key aspect of information theory (cs.IT). The vulnerabilities in the pilot sequence design and the proposed attacking strategy are related to network security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the impact of the attacking strategy on the signal-to-interference-plus-noise ratio (SINR) requirements of the users, which is a key performance metric in networked systems (cs.NI). The use of massive MIMO technology and the impact of the attacking strategy on the per-cell user load region are related to multimedia systems (cs.MM) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
